1
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:41,399
You say he owes you money

2
00:00:41,399 --> 00:00:42,560
but you're not the least bit worried.

3
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:43,920
He... he owes me money.

4
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:44,759
Director Ge

5
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,600
About our severance pay...

6
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,880
Tell him to get the hell out, now!

7
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:51,240
What are you guys doing here?

8
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:53,960
Zhu Yihai!

9
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:54,719
We're screwed!

10
00:00:54,719 --> 00:00:55,200
Run!

11
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:06,799
How long are you gonna stand there?

12
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:17,959
Let me.

13
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,920
You're pretty impressive.

14
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,680
Sixty thousand yuan, sorted in two days.

15
00:01:24,799 --> 00:01:26,200
I haven't sorted it out.

16
00:01:31,079 --> 00:01:31,680
Drop it.

17
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:34,680
Have a seat.

18
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,079
What'll you have?

19
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:38,719
I'm not here to eat.

20
00:01:38,719 --> 00:01:40,680
I'm here to ask you something.

21
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,560
Go ahead.

22
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:51,120
What's the deal with Dao Balian?

23
00:01:51,519 --> 00:01:53,040
Why's he against me at every turn?

24
00:01:53,359 --> 00:01:54,680
He gave you trouble again?

25
00:01:54,959 --> 00:01:56,280
You bet.

26
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,560
I went to Director Ge

27
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,120
to ask for the severance pay.

28
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,280
How did I ever offend him?

29
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,480
Zhu Yihai, are you

30
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,520
really clueless or just faking it?

31
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:11,800
Wasn't I...

32
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,039
Wasn't my head

33
00:02:13,039 --> 00:02:14,000
messed up for a bit?

34
00:02:14,199 --> 00:02:15,879
You don't seem like your head's messed up.

35
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,520
You seem like a completely different person.

36
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:21,159
Me? No way.

37
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,840
How could I be someone else?

38
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,120
That's impossible.

39
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,479
But you do have a point.

40
00:02:26,759 --> 00:02:28,360
We've been laid off for two years.

41
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,319
Ge Zhendong really should

42
00:02:29,319 --> 00:02:30,520
give us an explanation.

43
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:33,599
Tell you what.

44
00:02:34,159 --> 00:02:35,319
Tomorrow, you go to the factory office.

45
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:36,400
Leave the rest to me.

46
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:46,759
Comrades,

47
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,120
our factory has faced some challenges lately.

48
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,439
But it's precisely these challenges

49
00:02:52,879 --> 00:02:56,000
that prove our resilience and unity.

50
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,360
I hope none of you lose heart.

51
00:02:58,759 --> 00:03:02,319
I know in times like these,

52
00:03:02,319 --> 00:03:04,719
rumors are bound to spread.

53
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,039
And all of you

54
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:09,400
must've heard some inaccurate news.

55
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,840
What I want to emphasize is

56
00:03:11,159 --> 00:03:13,319
we must stay positive.

57
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:15,120
Hardships are temporary.

58
00:03:15,639 --> 00:03:17,039
The future of our factory

59
00:03:17,039 --> 00:03:18,319
is still very bright.

60
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,560
Who are you people?

61
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,599
He doesn't remember us yet.

62
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,360
Old Luo,

63
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:31,520
if you're short on money,

64
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,479
just tell me!

65
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,319
Ge Zhendong!

66
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,680
Ge Zhendong!

67
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,240
Zhu Yihai.

68
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,439
That's me.

69
00:03:40,879 --> 00:03:41,639
Director Ge,

70
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,879
hello there.

71
00:03:48,919 --> 00:03:49,639
What do you want?

72
00:03:49,759 --> 00:03:50,479
What do you guys want?

73
00:03:50,719 --> 00:03:52,240
You know why I'm here.

74
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,520
Just give the word

75
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,680
and I'll leave right away.

76
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,680
Impossible.

77
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:57,280
Absolutely impossible.

78
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,360
Zhu Yihai,

79
00:04:01,319 --> 00:04:02,879
it's not too late for you to leave now.

80
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:06,120
If you get carried out of here later,

81
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,560
it won't be pretty.

82
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,960
Well, let's see

83
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,800
before they get here,

84
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,120
if you'll still be alive.

85
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:13,879
Dali!

86
00:04:22,199 --> 00:04:23,160
Zhu Yihai!

87
00:04:23,399 --> 00:04:24,959
You ungrateful traitor!

88
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,199
Coming here to stir up trouble!

89
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:29,199
Zhu Yihai!

90
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:31,240
You couldn't take me down earlier,

91
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:32,680
and now you wanna leave?

92
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:34,199
You're not going anywhere.

93
00:04:39,199 --> 00:04:40,199
Zhu Yihai.

94
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,319
I just don't get it.

95
00:04:43,439 --> 00:04:44,639
How am I, Dao Balian,

96
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,360
any worse than you?

97
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:47,800
You're just a laid-off worker.

98
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,399
Why is everyone helping you?

99
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:51,079
I haven't even come after you yet.

100
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:53,240
And you have the nerve to come to us?

101
00:04:53,639 --> 00:04:55,600
The wise and mighty Director Ge,

102
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:56,920
Chief Dao.

103
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,319
Make your move.

104
00:04:59,120 --> 00:04:59,720
Director Ge,

105
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,920
what do we do?

106
00:05:02,639 --> 00:05:04,040
Let's see how this plays out.

107
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,199
Or they'll come back even worse tomorrow.

108
00:05:06,519 --> 00:05:07,040
Relax.

109
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,759
Today I'll make them realize

110
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:10,920
who they truly are.

111
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,680
So they'll never dare come back.

112
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:15,319
Make them feel ashamed of themselves.

113
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:17,399
Just look at our Director Ge.

114
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,519
Dignified and handsome,

115
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:20,959
wise and mighty.

116
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:21,959
Now look at yourselves.

117
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:24,319
You two are dressed like peacocks.

118
00:05:24,759 --> 00:05:25,439
And you.

119
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:26,639
You big dumb lug.

120
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:27,439
Shifty eyes!

121
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:28,399
What are you looking at?

122
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,519
Do you know

123
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:31,879
how much Director Ge

124
00:05:31,879 --> 00:05:33,240
has poured his heart and soul

125
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,360
into our employees?

126
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:37,639
What a brown-noser.

127
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,879
You don't know shit.

128
00:05:38,879 --> 00:05:39,879
You have no idea

129
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:41,680
about Director Ge's silent dedication.

130
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:44,120
Take Little Wang in our security section.

131
00:05:44,839 --> 00:05:46,759
Little Wang's family is so poor.

132
00:05:46,759 --> 00:05:47,920
Every spring,

133
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,560
his mom transfers from a train

134
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:52,000
to a coach, then to a city bus,

135
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,439
just to bring him a few

136
00:05:53,439 --> 00:05:54,680
frozen pears from home.

137
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,879
Those frozen pears are so sweet.

138
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:57,079
Absolutely delicious.

139
00:05:57,959 --> 00:05:59,040
But if you eat too many,

140
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,279
you get a Splitting headache.

141
00:06:00,519 --> 00:06:01,720
So our Director Ge,

142
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,319
for Little Wang's health,

143
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,000
devoured every last one of them.

144
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:09,680
Completely ignoring his own blood sugar.

145
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,759
I'd rather give myself a Splitting headache.

146
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,120
And his distant relative Little Li.

147
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,519
Been a bachelor for so many years.

148
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,879
Finally got a blind date set up.

149
00:06:17,879 --> 00:06:19,240
Saved up months of wages

150
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,439
to buy a necktie.

151
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:21,800
Just to make a good impression

152
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,720
on his date.

153
00:06:24,839 --> 00:06:25,720
Director Ge.

154
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:28,040
To stamp out Little Li's materialism,

155
00:06:29,439 --> 00:06:30,800
he led by example.

156
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,639
And that very day, he swiped the tie.

157
00:06:32,639 --> 00:06:33,600
We absolutely can't let

158
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,959
this kind of bad social habit

159
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:36,399
spread into our factory.

160
00:06:38,279 --> 00:06:39,600
Chief Dao, that's enough.

161
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,319
How can I stop?

162
00:06:41,879 --> 00:06:42,879
I've got more to say.

163
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:45,079
There's also

164
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:46,439
Little Zhang from Workshop One,

165
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:47,800
Little Sun from Workshop Two,

166
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,439
Qi the Know-it-all from Workshop Four.

167
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:51,399
He sorted them all out perfectly.

168
00:06:51,399 --> 00:06:52,199
Last month,

169
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,439
to keep our factory employees

170
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:55,680
from getting unbalanced nutrition,

171
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:58,439
Director Ge personally revised the menu.

172
00:06:58,439 --> 00:07:01,279
So you all eat more veggies and less meat.

173
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:04,199
The infamous ladle shake.

174
00:07:04,199 --> 00:07:05,279
How brilliant.

175
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,199
He's not just Director Ge!

176
00:07:13,959 --> 00:07:15,839
He's a truly great director!

177
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,120
Dao Balian.

178
00:07:17,839 --> 00:07:18,519
What the hell are you doing?

179
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:19,759
Director Ge,

180
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,680
I'm just letting them know

181
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,279
about all the good deeds you've done.

182
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,600
That's right, Director Ge.

183
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,240
You've done so many good deeds.

184
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,160
Why don't you tell us yourself?

185
00:07:27,839 --> 00:07:29,639
No, no, I didn't do anything!

186
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:31,959
Were you the one who cut our wages earlier?

187
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:33,240
That really wasn't my doing.

188
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,800
That was all Accountant Liu's idea.

189
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,600
I...

190
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,560
Then don't tell me

191
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,399
this severance pay business

192
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,639
was also Accountant Liu's doing?

193
00:07:41,639 --> 00:07:43,639
Yes, it was all him.

194
00:07:43,639 --> 00:07:44,959
I had no idea at all!

195
00:07:44,959 --> 00:07:45,839
Director Ge,

196
00:07:45,839 --> 00:07:47,199
let's call Accountant Liu right now

197
00:07:47,199 --> 00:07:48,199
and have a word with him.

198
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,519
Put it on speaker.

199
00:07:54,319 --> 00:07:54,800
You...

200
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:57,040
Good thing I set up a code with Accountant Liu.

201
00:08:00,839 --> 00:08:01,839
Accountant Liu,

202
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,040
this is Director Ge.

203
00:08:03,879 --> 00:08:04,519
Director Ge.

204
00:08:04,639 --> 00:08:05,439
Listen to me,

205
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,279
right now,

206
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:08,920
the situation is urgent.

207
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,160
The severance pay,

208
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,720
pay it to them,

209
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,560
and settle it.

210
00:08:12,759 --> 00:08:13,160
Okay,

211
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,399
no problem.

212
00:08:16,439 --> 00:08:17,319
Accountant Liu,

213
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:19,480
you might not have heard me clearly.

214
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:21,040
What I said was,

215
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,759
the situation is urgent.

216
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:23,639
I heard you clearly this time.

217
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,639
Tell them to come to the finance office immediately.

218
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:26,959
We'll handle the paperwork later.

219
00:08:26,959 --> 00:08:27,680
Settle the accounts right away.

220
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:28,839
No, no, no.

221
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:29,839
Accountant Liu,

222
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,720
does the factory still have money in its accounts?

223
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,399
Yes, we do.

224
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:35,759
We've got plenty to spare.

225
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:36,799
Accountant Liu,

226
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:39,159
let's also pay back the severance

227
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:39,919
we owed others before.

228
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,440
No problem.

229
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:41,440
We'll make up for all of it.

230
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:43,039
We won't owe a single penny.

231
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,720
I'll be waiting in the finance office.

232
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,240
There, problem solved, right?

233
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,200
Now hurry up and apologize.

234
00:08:49,559 --> 00:08:50,279
Director Ge,

235
00:08:50,799 --> 00:08:52,240
I really didn't expect it to go this smoothly.

236
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:52,960
So I...

237
00:08:53,279 --> 00:08:54,120
my apologies.

238
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,320
No, no, no need.

239
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:56,919
Just now,

240
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:57,879
this little microphone,

241
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:59,320
I shouldn't have turned it on for you.

242
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,159
What?

243
00:09:00,279 --> 00:09:00,840
Turn it off.

244
00:09:01,159 --> 00:09:02,000
Wait, you...

245
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,639
Dig in!

246
00:09:15,559 --> 00:09:17,519
What's wrong, Dali? Stunned?

247
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:19,679
I'm not eating.

248
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:20,799
We've got money now.

249
00:09:21,759 --> 00:09:23,960
Just looking at these buns makes me happy.

250
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,799
You goofball.

251
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,879
Let me see yours.

252
00:09:27,879 --> 00:09:29,000
Not showing you.

253
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,720
Brother Hai bought it for me.

254
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:33,200
You two, knock it off.

255
00:09:33,559 --> 00:09:35,279
We've already pissed off Director Ge.

256
00:09:35,559 --> 00:09:37,000
What if he does something to us later?

257
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:40,240
That severance pay was owed to us in the first place.

258
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,200
Can he really take it back?

259
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,360
What I'm wondering is, why Dao Balian

260
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,039
suddenly decided to help us.

261
00:09:46,799 --> 00:09:48,639
It's gotta be because of Sister Qian.

262
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:52,799
Qian Huilian tipped off Dao Balian.

263
00:09:52,799 --> 00:09:54,320
Those two have always had something fishy going on.

264
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:55,279
Lili.

265
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:56,440
You shouldn't say that.

266
00:09:56,799 --> 00:09:58,120
Without Dao Balian,

267
00:09:58,519 --> 00:09:59,919
we wouldn't have gotten this money.

268
00:09:59,919 --> 00:10:01,840
Stop calling me Lili all the time.

269
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:03,440
Call me Sister-in-law.

270
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,679
Show some respect.

271
00:10:05,399 --> 00:10:06,600
I've got more good news.

272
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:07,720
Wanna hear it?

273
00:10:11,799 --> 00:10:15,240
Once word got out about free comics with memberships,

274
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:17,840
our pool hall got mobbed.

275
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:19,879
We made money!

276
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,799
You bet!

277
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:21,759
How much?

278
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:24,960
A thousand bucks.

279
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,600
A thousand, my ass.

280
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,879
Ten thousand!

281
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,279
Holy crap!

282
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:31,879
We're all Millionaires now!

283
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,440
Drink up!

284
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,480
Cheers!

285
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,919
To think I'd see this day!

286
00:10:48,559 --> 00:10:49,720
Wow!

287
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:52,279
Awesome!

288
00:10:53,879 --> 00:10:55,519
Hey, why are you dodging drinks?

289
00:10:55,519 --> 00:10:56,200
